We are seeking Process Operators to join our Oil Sands operations in three different areas. Our asset expansion plans are ramping up and creating multiple quality opportunities for Process Operators at the established Long Lake SAGD facility, where we are preparing for Partial Upgrading plant restart as well as restarting our Kinosis 1A Steam Generation facility (K1A).

This position is classified as a Safety-Sensitive Position. You will be working a 7 on  7 off shift, days and nights (subject to change). As a Fort McMurray based Process Operator, you will ensure the safe and efficient operation of the plant process equipment. This includes interacting with and supporting the Maintenance, Technical, and Health, Safety, Environmental and Social Responsibility teams within the Oilsands Division of the North American business.

As a CNOOC International Process Operator your contributions will include, but not be limited to,

Adhering and enforcing safety policies and procedures;
Applying and developing equipment lockouts;
Issuing and managing safe work permits;
Environmental stewardship;
Operating equipment within established parameters per established procedures;
Supporting/responding to unit operations and equipment requirements, including Shift Turnover, start of Shift Orientation, troubleshooting, and Defined Rounds;
Communicating between the Control Room Operator (CRO) and on shift operator;
Conducting assigned activities in accordance to approved directives and procedures;
Run to Target, report deviations in the e-log and escalate to Maintenance/Technical/Production for assistance as required;
Managing abnormal situations by initiating a controlled hierarchy of Stabilize/Slowdown/Shutdown (SSS);
Participating in and completing required training to achieve a high level of understanding and competency;
Adhering to CNOOC International's Drug and Alcohol Policy;
Adhering to all principles of the Production Department Operations Excellence Process;
A member of the Emergency Response Team (ERT).

Who are we looking for?

As the ideal candidate, you will thrive in our dynamic work environment by displaying a positive attitude and the flexibility necessary to manage multiple priorities and challenges. It goes without saying that you have a zero-tolerance attitude towards shortcuts and are uncompromising when it comes to ensuring tasks are done safely. You are an alert problem solver who learns to anticipate and solve potential issues before they arise. The following skills, competencies and qualifications will position you for future success with CNOOC International:

An inter-provincial 3rd class Power Engineering Certificate valid for Alberta;
Minimum of 5 years of plant/field experience, preferably in an Upgrader or Refinery setting;
Experience in hands-on support of operations technical, and maintenance work teams;
Have the ability to comprehend a situation and identify underlying causes, use knowledge and experience to tackle the issues;
Experience in developing standard operating procedures;
Strong organization planning and new infrastructure development skills;
Commissioning and start up experience would be an asset;
Must have MS Office skills (Word, Excel and Outlook);
Good written and verbal communication;
A valid Class 5 drivers license is required;
Must be legally permitted to work in Canada.

